description: Genova Property Group AB owns, manages, and develops real estate. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 26 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2015-12-15. The firm owns, manages, and develops properties with focus on the Stockholm and Uppsala. The Company’s activities are structured into three divisions: Investment properties, which consists commercial areas, such as schools, municipalities, counties and the defense industry; Housing, in which the Company develops residential and rental properties, and Public Buildings, which develop solutions for nursing and care homes.
